<DOC><DOCNO> AP890905-0193 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-05-89 1206EDT</FILEID><FIRST>a a BC-PRI--LicenseRequirements Adv07   09-05 0306</FIRST><SECOND>BC-PRI--License Requirements, Adv 07,0325</SECOND><HEAD>$adv07</HEAD><HEAD>For release Thursday, Sept. 7, and thereafter</HEAD><HEAD>States' Age-Based Driver License and Renewal Requirements</HEAD><HEAD>With BC-PRI--Older Drivers, BC-PRI--Drivers-Program</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Here is a list of age-based licensing andrenewal procedures as of last January, based on an April report bythe National Highway Traffic Safety Administration.   No age-specific requirements were reported for the other states.</TEXT><TEXT>   ALASKA: No good-driver renewal-by-mail or test waivers at 70.   ARIZONA: No good-driver renewal-by-mail or test waivers at 70.   CALIFORNIA: No good-driver renewal-by-mail or test waivers at 70.   DISTRICT OF COLUMBIA: Knowledge and road tests for renewal after75; reaction test for renewal at 70.   HAWAII: License renewal every two years after 65, every 4 yearsfor others.   ILLINOIS: Under legislation signed into law Aug. 31, licenserenewal starting in 1990 will be every two years for those 81-86,every year for 87 and above, every four years for others; road testfor license or renewal at 75, effective immediately.   INDIANA: License renewal every three years after 75, every fouryears for others; road skills test for renewal after 75.   IOWA: Renewal every two years after 70, every four years forothers.   LOUISIANA: Renewal every two years after 70, every five years forothers.   MAINE: Vision test for renewal at 40 and 52 and each renewalafter 65.   MARYLAND: Medical report for new drivers at 70 and above.   NEW HAMPSHIRE: Knowledge and road skills tests for renewal after75.   NEW MEXICO: Renewal every year after 75, every four years forothers.   OREGON: Vision test at renewal over 50.   PENNSYLVANIA: Physical examination for a sample of renewalapplicants over 45 (usually the drivers are over 65.)   RHODE ISLAND: Renewal every two years after 70, every five yearsfor others.   UTAH: No good-driver vision test waiver at renewal over 65.</TEXT><NOTE>End Adv for Sept. 7</NOTE></DOC>